condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :5.01 (a) | Description :All four countries sign a subsidiary agreement with regional organization (CSRP) | DueDate :26-Feb-2010
Finance Agreement :5.01 (c) | Description :All four countries have adopted Operational Manuals including national action plans forthe regional process framework | Due Date :26-Feb-2010
Finance Agreement :5.01 (d) | Description :National PIUs and steering committees established in all 4 countries, includingrecruitment of coordinators | Due Date :26-Feb-2010

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 Section D1: A work plan, satisfactory to the Association, specifying the measures taken, or to betaken in compliance with the Social and Environmental Safeguard Framework and Instruments, as such frameworks and instruments maybe applicable to the activities under Part A.3(b) and A.3(c) of the Project .
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 Section D1: Detailed eligibility criteria, and terms and conditions of the grants and micro-creditsunder Part A.3(b) and A.3(c) of the Project
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I.G | Description :All MCS activities by Program are reviewed periodically by an independentgroup of experts | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I.G | Description :All fisheries surveillance activities are carried out by civilianauthorities under TORs limited to fisheries surveillance | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I.G | Description :All goods, works, services and op. costs financed by Program are usedexclusively by civilian authorities for Program, not for military purpose or criminal proceedings | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I.G | Description :CSRP will ensure that activities under component 2 are reviewed by anindependent group of experts 24, 36 and 60 months after effectiveness | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I.G | Description :Each fisheries surveillance mission financed by Program shall be undercommand or authority of civilian officer and time-bound and mission-specific, duly recorded and documented | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I.G | Description :In Sierra Leone the Ministry of Fisheries maintains throughout theProgram the Fisheries Protection Unit in the JMC, exclusively dedicated to fisheries surveillance | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section IV.B | Description :For Sierra Leone, no funds are disbursed for component 2 until currentregulation has been revised concerning fisheries surveillance and the Fisheries Protetion Unit is established | Due Date:15-Jun-2010

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section IV.B | Description :For all countries, no funds will be disbursed for regional activitiesunder component 4, until the regional coordination unit and regional steering committee have been established by the CSRP | DueDate :26-Feb-2010

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section IV.B | Description :In Senegal, no funds will be disbursed for a sub-project in component 1until the appropriate sub-financing agreement for each sub-project has been concluded | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section IV.B | Description :No funds disbursed for component 2 in Liberia until a new regulationadopted clarifying scope of Fisheries Act and responsibility of BNF for fisheries surveillance, consistent with UNCLOS | Due Date:15-Jun-2010

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section V.1 | Description :For Cape Verde, Liberia and Sierra Leone, the accountant/assistantaccountant and procurement specialist for national PIU have been recruited | Due Date :30-Jun-2010
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section V.1 | Description :For all four countries and CSRP, external auditors are appointed, andaccounting software installed or updated | Due Date :30-Jun-2010
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section V.1 | Description :In Liberia an assistant internal audior is recruited | Due Date:15-Jun-2010

title.narrative: Pilot integrated fish landing site clusters established by the Program and operating in each country
Total number of Territorial Use Rights Fisheries (TURFs) legally established for coastal fisheries in the four countries
Increase or stabilization in the volume of exports from targeted fisheries in the 4 countries
Communities that are allocated fishing rights
Small-scale fishing vessels in targeted fisheries that are registered
Total patrol days at sea per year in targeted fisheries
Fishing vessels observed by aerial/surface patrol or by radar and satellite monitoring, that are committing a serious infraction intargeted fisheries
A competent sanitary authority (CA) is accredited for certification of exports to the European Union in Liberia
A regional database and 'dashboard' of key environmental, economic and social fisheries statistics is established at the CSRP
A regional fishing vessel registry is operating at the CSRP
A satellite-based fishing vessel monitoring system (VMS) is in place and functioning
Clear principles and policies are established to increase the wealth from fisheries through strengthened rights and equitable allocation of these rights which balances economic efficiency
GEO and PDO Indicators are the same
